It's time to tear our bedroom apart. The last room in the house where, apart from a bit of decorating, nothing else has been done.
The ugly electric fireplace and the hearth floor must go. We need to enclose the fireplace, replace the chipped plaster, and smooth it out. Then build a custom wardrobe.
We always start with a rough pencil sketch…
The dirty part of the job is done.
We found a few dead birds in the chimney, very dry :(
Everything ready for the plasterer next week
The small side niche has turned out well
Here comes a new wardrobe in (but we haven't even started with the design yet 🙈)
Oh, look what we found behind the heater!
And we've even thought about installing this nice little air vent, so the fireplace doesn't get damp
The chimney sweep has installed the cover and cap. Now it should be a bit safer for the ravens that like to nest up there🪺
The plasterer is done. Tomorrow the floor will be laid!
The cork underlay is laid, I've made a toilet paper roll sawdust extractor for the vacuum cleaner 😂
Floor parts are ready and can be laid. We're having a tea break right now.
Buhu. Today things are moving slowly because of super complicated cuts around the doorposts to ensure a smooth transition to the hallway (where the floor will also be re-laid). @user45@twitter.com cursed me
Done, but at the end! The crowning glory was the terrible assembly instructions for the new bed. We'll sleep well tonight!
The floor in the hallway and all the baseboards are still missing. The decorator will come in a month, so we currently have a raw plaster look.
A bit more DIY work in the evening to cut or chisel the lower sections around the doorposts, where the floor will then fit seamlessly underneath.
The cork underlay is now also in the hallway.
We finished the hallway floor yesterday! Then out at 5 a.m. to pick up Item 1 at Heathrow, then a nap and final push in the hallway, the baseboards are installed. Joints will be made once the adhesive is dry.
